Create a GitHub Actions workflow to deploy the jobBot Python app and run it every day at 7 AM UTC.

The workflow should:
- trigger on schedule and manual dispatch
- checkout the repository
- set up Python 3.14
- install dependencies from requirements.txt
- create a .env file from repository secrets
- run python main.py
- upload logs as artifacts for debugging

Use the following repo secrets: TELEGRAM_TOKEN, CHAT_ID, RSS_URLS, INSTAGRAM_ACCOUNTS, COMPANY_CAREER_PAGES, JOB_KEYWORDS.

Also note that GitHub Actions runners are ephemeral, so local SQLite state (jobs.db) does not persist between runs unless external persistence is added.